WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:05.797
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:05.880 --> 00:06.881
<i>kids:</i>
<i>Pig!</i>

00:06.965 --> 00:10.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:10.176 --> 00:10.552
<i>Goat!</i>

00:10.635 --> 00:13.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:13.555 --> 00:14.806
<i>Banana!</i>

00:14.889 --> 00:19.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:19.561 --> 00:20.770
<i>Cricket!</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:28.153
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:33.533 --> 00:35.160
- A-a-a-achoo!

00:35.243 --> 00:38.413
<i>all:</i>
<i>Pig! Goat! Banana! Cricket!</i>

00:41.750 --> 00:44.753
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

00:44.836 --> 00:52.927
<i>♪</i> ♪

00:53.011 --> 00:56.097
[all chewing and slurping]

00:58.099 --> 01:00.560
- Friends,
I have an announcement.

01:00.643 --> 01:04.730
Behold, the ultimate
master remote control.

01:04.813 --> 01:08.151
Whoever controls
this sleek titanium beauty

01:08.234 --> 01:09.944
becomes King of TV!

01:10.028 --> 01:11.988
Or, you know, Queen of TV.

01:12.071 --> 01:13.114
- Aw!

01:13.198 --> 01:15.033
{\an3}- What do you mean,
"King of TV"?

01:15.116 --> 01:17.202
- It means you can watch
whatever you want

01:17.285 --> 01:18.536
wherever you want.

01:18.620 --> 01:20.497
It doesn't even
have to be a show!

01:20.580 --> 01:24.292
{\an3}Like, we can all watch
The Goat Channel.

01:24.375 --> 01:25.877
- [chewing]

01:25.960 --> 01:29.339
- "All Goat All the Time."

01:29.422 --> 01:31.341
{\an3}- Hey, I like
The Goat Channel.

01:31.424 --> 01:34.427
- Ooh, I want to watch
"Pickler on the Roof."

01:36.179 --> 01:37.764
- ♪ If I were a pickle ♪

01:37.847 --> 01:39.974
♪ Oinky boinky doinky doo ♪

01:40.058 --> 01:42.352
- My life is complete.

01:42.435 --> 01:44.604
{\an1}- Hello, yoo-hoo,
bing bong, good morning!

01:44.687 --> 01:46.564
{\an1}I think we were all
enjoying The Goat Channel.

01:46.648 --> 01:47.941
I know I was.

01:48.942 --> 01:50.026
- No,
we're not

01:50.109 --> 01:52.529
all enjoying
The Goat Channel.

01:53.613 --> 01:54.697
- I was.

01:54.781 --> 01:55.907
- I'm the true King of TV,

01:55.990 --> 01:58.785
and we all want to watch...

01:58.868 --> 02:01.621
"Hobo Pajama Dance Party!"

02:01.704 --> 02:04.874
{\an1}Man, look at those hobos
hoboin' to the oldies.

02:04.958 --> 02:07.293
[all arguing and shouting]

02:09.127 --> 02:10.338
- [screeches]

02:11.631 --> 02:12.924
- Ah!

02:13.007 --> 02:14.592
- Oh man,
I hate that falcon.

02:14.676 --> 02:15.218
- [sputters]

02:15.301 --> 02:17.011
After that remote!

02:17.095 --> 02:18.763
[all grunting]

02:18.847 --> 02:20.640
- King of TV, here I come!

02:22.183 --> 02:25.979
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:26.062 --> 02:27.272
- [screeches]

02:27.355 --> 02:28.523
- Please give me back

02:28.606 --> 02:30.775
the shiny remote,
Mr. Giant Falcon.

02:30.859 --> 02:31.818
Please!

02:31.901 --> 02:33.528
- [humming]

02:33.611 --> 02:35.238
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:35.321 --> 02:36.239
- Angry Old Raisin!

02:36.322 --> 02:37.740
You'll help me.

02:37.824 --> 02:39.826
You're my fourth best friend
in the whole world.

02:39.909 --> 02:41.786
- I ain't helping you!

02:41.870 --> 02:45.081
I'm taking a relaxing vacation
in the Caribbean,

02:45.164 --> 02:48.626
far away from your buffoonery.

02:48.710 --> 02:50.587
- Oh, please?

02:50.670 --> 02:52.755
- No.

02:52.839 --> 02:53.882
{\an1}- Please help me get
the remote from the falcon.

02:53.965 --> 02:55.800
{\an1}Be a pal--
[grunts]

02:55.884 --> 02:57.677
I'll call you.

02:57.760 --> 02:58.678
- You can't!

02:58.761 --> 02:59.679
I changed my number!

02:59.762 --> 03:00.722
- Is it five?

03:00.805 --> 03:01.723
{\an3}- No.

03:01.806 --> 03:02.724
- Is it six?

03:02.807 --> 03:03.683
{\an3}- No.

03:03.766 --> 03:04.642
- Eight?
- No.

03:04.726 --> 03:06.185
There is no eight.

03:07.645 --> 03:10.189
{\an1}- Looks like I'm gonna
have to do this on my own.

03:10.273 --> 03:11.441
I'll just have to catch you

03:11.524 --> 03:14.444
{\an1}the same way everyone
catches falcons.

03:14.527 --> 03:16.279
With a fishing pole!

03:16.362 --> 03:18.323
This is perfect
for bird hooking.

03:20.533 --> 03:23.286
Ah!
[screams]

03:23.369 --> 03:24.537
Whee!

03:24.621 --> 03:26.789
I'm horrifically terrified,
but whee!

03:26.873 --> 03:28.249
Yippee!

03:28.333 --> 03:31.628
Ah, finally,
I've got two relaxing weeks

03:31.711 --> 03:34.380
without that
infernal Pig annoying me.

03:34.464 --> 03:36.257
- Angry Old Raisin!

03:36.341 --> 03:37.508
I knew he'd help!

03:37.592 --> 03:38.468
{\an3}[laughs]

03:38.551 --> 03:39.928
- No!

03:40.011 --> 03:42.221
[passengers screaming]

03:42.305 --> 03:46.643
- I just wanted
to go on vacation.

03:46.726 --> 03:48.561
I'm old!

03:48.645 --> 03:49.103
{\an3}- Yoink.

03:49.187 --> 03:51.105
- [screams]

03:51.189 --> 03:54.651
Please, leave me alone!

03:54.734 --> 03:56.444
- [screeches]

03:56.527 --> 03:57.820
- [gasps]
That's it!

03:57.904 --> 04:00.782
Yes, I'll leave you alone
as bait.

04:00.865 --> 04:02.825
{\an1}- Me?
Bait?

04:02.909 --> 04:06.037
{\an1}- Relax, pal,
you're safe with me!

04:06.120 --> 04:09.457
{\an1}When the falcon flies by,
I'll catch him with my net.

04:09.540 --> 04:11.334
- Huh?
- [screams]

04:11.417 --> 04:12.585
{\an1}- Um...

04:12.669 --> 04:13.211
{\an1}[gasps]

04:13.294 --> 04:15.296
Angry Old Raisin!

04:15.380 --> 04:17.798
- I don't agree
with your ways!

04:17.882 --> 04:19.216
[muffled shouting]
- [swallows]

04:19.300 --> 04:20.343
- [screams]

04:20.426 --> 04:21.010
Don't worry, Raisin!

04:21.094 --> 04:23.179
I'm a-comin'!

04:23.262 --> 04:28.351
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:28.434 --> 04:31.688
Give me my
fourth best friend back!

04:31.771 --> 04:32.730
- [screeches]

04:32.814 --> 04:34.399
- Everything's
gonna be okay.

04:34.482 --> 04:35.650
[thunk]
[screams]

04:35.733 --> 04:38.486
Raisin?

04:38.569 --> 04:40.113
[sobbing]

04:40.196 --> 04:41.656
Raisin?

04:41.739 --> 04:43.366
[crying]

04:43.449 --> 04:46.286
No remote
and no Raisin.

04:46.369 --> 04:48.871
Fourth best friend
in the whole wide world?

04:48.955 --> 04:51.958
[sobbing]

04:59.340 --> 05:01.384
- [panting]

05:01.467 --> 05:03.386
- [gasps]
Angry Old Raisin!

05:03.469 --> 05:04.887
You're alive.

05:04.971 --> 05:06.848
- [whimpers]

05:06.931 --> 05:08.224
Yes, I am...

05:08.307 --> 05:09.767
unfortunately.

05:09.851 --> 05:11.144
And what
in the blazes is this?

05:11.227 --> 05:14.063
- [gasps]
The remote!

05:14.147 --> 05:15.857
We're King of TV!

05:15.940 --> 05:17.066
Yippee!

05:17.150 --> 05:20.236
- More like
Queen of TV.

05:20.319 --> 05:21.863
{\an3}[laughs]

05:21.946 --> 05:23.948
{\an3}Whoa!

05:24.032 --> 05:25.825
- Bye, Goat.

05:27.410 --> 05:29.412
- [grunting]

05:29.495 --> 05:31.706
Come to Mama Goat,
you beautiful remote con--

05:31.789 --> 05:33.583
[grunts]

05:33.666 --> 05:35.126
[stammering]

05:35.209 --> 05:37.545
- Dollar toll to pass.

05:37.628 --> 05:40.173
- Oh, well, you're
mistaken, dear sir.

05:40.256 --> 05:41.382
I am not here to pass.

05:41.466 --> 05:43.342
{\an1}I just need to grab
that--[grunts]

05:43.426 --> 05:45.094
- Dollar toll to pass.

05:45.178 --> 05:45.803
- But it's right there.

05:45.887 --> 05:47.930
Inches away.

05:48.014 --> 05:51.684
{\an1}All I have to do is
reach over there and--ow!

05:51.768 --> 05:54.395
- No tolley, no passey.

05:54.479 --> 05:55.855
- Fling flang dung nugget--

05:55.938 --> 05:58.900
[barrier thumping]

05:58.983 --> 06:00.234
{\an1}[growls]

06:00.318 --> 06:01.444
[grunts]

06:01.527 --> 06:03.738
- Har, har, har.

06:03.821 --> 06:06.532
Leapin' Liberty,
that's rich.

06:06.616 --> 06:09.535
- Hello, Thomas Jefferson.

06:09.619 --> 06:11.704
{\an3}- You know, you'll never
get past that booth

06:11.788 --> 06:13.539
without paying that toll.

06:13.623 --> 06:14.874
{\an3}I've been
trying all day

06:14.957 --> 06:18.169
{\an3}to get my diary back
from Alexander Hamilton.

06:18.252 --> 06:19.796
{\an3}Hamilton!

06:19.879 --> 06:21.422
You and Betsy Ross, pfft!

06:21.506 --> 06:22.340
{\an3}[laughs]

06:22.423 --> 06:23.424
Good luck with that one.

06:23.508 --> 06:25.802
Oh!
- A full dollar toll?

06:25.885 --> 06:27.053
But I'm broke.

06:27.136 --> 06:27.929
- I'm broke too!

06:28.012 --> 06:29.722
[fly buzzing]

06:29.806 --> 06:31.015
{\an3}[chomps]

06:31.099 --> 06:33.976
{\an3}[chewing]

06:34.060 --> 06:36.646
{\an1}- It pains my very soul
to say this,

06:36.729 --> 06:39.398
but if we work together,

06:39.482 --> 06:41.776
{\an1}we could make
that money faster

06:41.859 --> 06:45.363
{\an1}and cross--
[groans]--together.

06:45.446 --> 06:47.698
- Sweet sassy Monticello.

06:47.782 --> 06:49.867
You mean,
you and me--

06:49.951 --> 06:51.869
[retches]

06:51.953 --> 06:53.204
Team up?

06:53.287 --> 06:55.164
[both retching]

06:55.248 --> 06:56.833
{\an3}I guess we have
no choice.

06:56.916 --> 06:58.626
{\an3}- A car!

06:58.709 --> 07:01.963
{\an1}Let's give it a sudsy
scrub down for some change.

07:02.046 --> 07:04.048
{\an1}Get out of those
colonial clamdiggers

07:04.132 --> 07:05.591
and into that booty suit.

07:05.675 --> 07:07.593
We got a dollar to make!

07:07.677 --> 07:08.302
- Do you know who I am?

07:08.386 --> 07:10.721
I'm on the nickel!

07:10.805 --> 07:12.098
[grunts]

07:12.181 --> 07:13.349
Booty suit.

07:13.432 --> 07:14.559
[sputtering]

07:14.642 --> 07:16.269
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

07:16.352 --> 07:17.520
Mm-hmm!

07:17.603 --> 07:18.896
- Mind if I borrow your wig?

07:18.980 --> 07:21.023
- Uh, I suppose.

07:21.107 --> 07:22.942
{\an1}[grunts]
Oh!

07:23.025 --> 07:25.611
- [humming]

07:25.695 --> 07:27.697
{\an1}- Mind if I
borrow those horns?

07:27.780 --> 07:28.614
- Eh, I guess so.

07:30.408 --> 07:32.535
[window squeaking]

07:32.618 --> 07:34.203
- Here's a dime.

07:34.287 --> 07:36.205
{\an3}Don't spend it all
in one place.

07:36.289 --> 07:38.207
[tires squeal]

07:38.291 --> 07:40.334
<i>♪</i> ♪

07:40.418 --> 07:41.419
- Hi, Tiny Goosey.

07:41.502 --> 07:42.670
Can you help us
raise the rest

07:42.753 --> 07:44.589
{\an1}of the money we need
for this toll?

07:44.672 --> 07:45.506
- I will,
if you make

07:45.590 --> 07:48.676
Eskimo kisses
with each other.

07:48.759 --> 07:53.014
{\an1}- Uh, you mean,
rub noses together?

07:53.097 --> 07:55.266
- Ugh, no way!

07:55.349 --> 07:57.935
- I guess you don't
want this quarter.

07:58.019 --> 07:58.895
{\an1}- Uh...

07:58.978 --> 08:00.730
- Ooh, okay.

08:00.813 --> 08:01.898
{\an1}- Okay.

08:01.981 --> 08:02.940
- Wes!

08:03.024 --> 08:04.942
- I suppose.

08:05.026 --> 08:07.195
[both murmuring]

08:07.278 --> 08:08.946
{\an1}[chuckles]
Tickles.

08:09.030 --> 08:10.948
{\an3}- [laughs]

08:11.032 --> 08:15.369
[both laughing]

08:15.453 --> 08:16.412
- Blegh!
All right!

08:16.495 --> 08:17.580
Enough already!

08:17.663 --> 08:18.998
You guys are weird.

08:19.081 --> 08:20.374
[engine revs]

08:20.458 --> 08:22.084
- You know, Jefferson,

08:22.168 --> 08:24.337
{\an3}I'm beginning to hate you
a little less.

08:24.420 --> 08:26.547
[tires screech]
both: Hmm?

08:26.631 --> 08:34.639
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:42.605 --> 08:44.982
[both laughing]

08:50.696 --> 08:52.031
- We did it,
Jeffy Weffy.

08:52.114 --> 08:53.658
We have the full dollar!

08:53.741 --> 08:56.369
- Correction: I have it!

08:56.452 --> 08:57.328
{\an3}- Hey!

08:57.411 --> 08:58.287
How could you?

08:58.371 --> 08:59.580
You wig wearin',

08:59.664 --> 09:01.290
ding dong fling flangin'
rogger rocka!

09:01.374 --> 09:03.125
- Presidential powers, baby.

09:03.209 --> 09:06.754
Have fun on this
side of the toll.

09:06.837 --> 09:07.755
[buzzer blaring]

09:07.838 --> 09:09.882
- Five cents short.

09:11.884 --> 09:13.844
- You raised the price?

09:13.928 --> 09:15.096
{\an1}But why?

09:15.179 --> 09:16.847
- I felt like it.

09:16.931 --> 09:18.307
- Five cents short, huh?

09:18.391 --> 09:20.559
I know where you can
find an extra nickel.

09:20.643 --> 09:23.980
{\an3}- [grunts]

09:24.063 --> 09:27.108
You'll pay for this, Goat.

09:27.191 --> 09:28.442
- Yes, I will...

09:28.526 --> 09:29.443
with you!

09:29.527 --> 09:30.569
Haha!

09:30.653 --> 09:31.654
- Ow!

09:31.737 --> 09:34.991
Somebody hit me
with a nickel.

09:35.074 --> 09:36.033
- Shello.

09:36.117 --> 09:37.243
High five.

09:37.326 --> 09:38.160
Yes!

09:38.244 --> 09:39.412
I'm the Queen of TV!

09:39.495 --> 09:41.163
- Jig's up, roomie.

09:41.247 --> 09:42.331
I'm the King of TV,

09:42.415 --> 09:46.586
{\an3}and I'm watching
"Hobo Pajama Dance Party."

09:46.669 --> 09:48.004
- The Goat Channel.

09:48.087 --> 09:50.006
- "Hobo Pajama Dance Party!"

09:50.089 --> 09:51.007
[horn bellows]

09:51.090 --> 09:53.134
{\an3}[screams]
Ow!

09:55.761 --> 09:57.221
[horn bellows]

09:57.305 --> 09:58.764
- [grunts]
Got it!

09:58.848 --> 09:59.682
Dang!

09:59.765 --> 10:00.933
Got it!
Dang!

10:01.017 --> 10:01.976
Got it!

10:02.059 --> 10:02.977
Dang!

10:03.060 --> 10:05.813
[grunting]

10:06.814 --> 10:09.817
<i>[bluegrass music]</i>

10:09.900 --> 10:12.194
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:12.278 --> 10:13.362
Where am I?

10:13.446 --> 10:15.031
- You got a brain concussion,

10:15.114 --> 10:17.658
and we is nursin' you
back to health.

10:17.742 --> 10:19.744
- You did that for me?

10:19.827 --> 10:21.120
[slurps]

10:21.203 --> 10:22.204
This is great.

10:22.288 --> 10:23.039
What's in it?

10:23.122 --> 10:26.334
- Oh, boiled tires and boots.

10:26.417 --> 10:27.209
[soup gurgling]

10:27.293 --> 10:29.337
- [spits]

10:29.420 --> 10:30.671
Oh, my goodness.

10:30.755 --> 10:32.131
Are you guys hobos?

10:32.214 --> 10:34.508
- Excuse me?

10:34.592 --> 10:35.760
Yes, we are.

10:35.843 --> 10:36.719
{\an1}- Awesome!

10:36.802 --> 10:37.928
I love hobos!

10:38.012 --> 10:39.722
[footsteps]
[all gasp]

10:43.059 --> 10:44.268
- You should be quiet.

10:44.352 --> 10:45.186
Shh.

10:45.269 --> 10:46.228
- But I didn't even--

10:46.312 --> 10:48.481
- Calm down.

10:48.564 --> 10:51.609
- Fee, fi, fo, flowbo,

10:51.692 --> 10:54.945
I smell a stinky hobo!

10:55.029 --> 10:58.074
Hmm, a new whoopin' stick.

10:58.157 --> 10:59.700
[slapping]

10:59.784 --> 11:00.618
- My remote!

11:00.701 --> 11:02.787
She's got my remote!

11:02.870 --> 11:03.412
- Give it up, brother.

11:03.496 --> 11:05.414
It's gone.

11:05.498 --> 11:06.999
She's the meanest,
nastiest,

11:07.083 --> 11:12.004
most vicious train conductor
in the whole county.

11:12.088 --> 11:15.216
- All we want to do
is ride for free.

11:15.299 --> 11:18.052
- There better not be
any freeloaders

11:18.135 --> 11:20.471
hitching a ride in here.

11:20.554 --> 11:23.057
Time for a whooping!

11:23.140 --> 11:25.101
Whoop, whoop, whoop!

11:25.184 --> 11:26.519
- [screams]

11:26.602 --> 11:30.314
<i>- No ticket, no ride!</i>

11:30.398 --> 11:33.275
[all grumbling]

11:33.359 --> 11:34.235
- Oh, come on, you guys.

11:34.318 --> 11:36.028
You got to get
my remote back!

11:36.112 --> 11:39.323
I'm just a little fruit
in a big train.

11:39.407 --> 11:40.199
Please?

11:40.282 --> 11:42.034
- Sorry,
getting things back

11:42.118 --> 11:44.453
from folks who'll
beat the crud out of us

11:44.537 --> 11:46.372
is not the hobo way!

11:46.455 --> 11:50.292
- That's rule number six
in the Hobo Constitution.

11:50.376 --> 11:53.712
{\an3}- Oh, that's just a roll
of toilet paper.

11:53.796 --> 11:57.133
{\an3}I guess I'll just
have to do it by myself.

11:57.216 --> 11:59.802
Don't try to stop me.

11:59.885 --> 12:02.138
{\an3}Here I go.

12:02.221 --> 12:05.015
I'm--I'm going.

12:08.394 --> 12:09.979
You got this, B-man.

12:10.062 --> 12:13.149
Just walk in,
take the remote, walk out.

12:13.232 --> 12:14.483
You're the man!

12:14.567 --> 12:17.486
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:17.570 --> 12:19.488
<i>♪</i> ♪

12:19.572 --> 12:21.574
- How dare you.

12:21.657 --> 12:24.535
[snoring]

12:24.618 --> 12:26.996
- You're the man.

12:27.079 --> 12:28.706
- [murmuring]
Fun tub.

12:28.789 --> 12:29.957
- [grunting]

12:30.040 --> 12:31.459
{\an3}- [screams]

12:31.542 --> 12:33.085
{\an1}- [grunts]

12:33.169 --> 12:36.046
{\an1}Want to watch "Hobo Pajama
Dance Party" with me?

12:36.130 --> 12:40.176
- How dare you try
and steal my whoopin' stick?

12:40.259 --> 12:42.094
You know what this
calls for.

12:42.178 --> 12:44.096
{\an1}- No, no, no, please,
not a whoopin'.

12:44.180 --> 12:45.848
{\an1}Anything but a whoop--
[screams]

12:45.931 --> 12:48.976
- Whoop, whoop, whoop,
wakataka, whoop!

12:49.059 --> 12:51.312
- [grunting]
- Whoop, whoop, whoop!

12:51.395 --> 12:53.022
- [screams]

12:53.105 --> 12:55.608
<i>[grunting]</i>

12:57.443 --> 12:59.069
Oh, nuts.

12:59.153 --> 13:00.196
- I told you.

13:00.279 --> 13:02.156
{\an3}Ain't worth
a silly remote.

13:02.239 --> 13:04.116
- It's not silly.

13:05.117 --> 13:06.327
Imagine a device

13:06.410 --> 13:08.704
that lets you
watch anything you want,

13:08.787 --> 13:09.705
anywhere!

13:09.788 --> 13:10.831
- Ooh.
- That's amazing!

13:10.915 --> 13:12.541
- Schnazz pizazz.

13:12.625 --> 13:14.251
- What's a device?

13:14.335 --> 13:16.295
- The point is,
if you hobos--

13:16.378 --> 13:19.924
no, we hobos--
band together,

13:20.007 --> 13:21.383
we can get the remote

13:21.467 --> 13:23.594
and get rid of Owl Woman Lady
once and for all!

13:23.677 --> 13:26.305
{\an3}- But how are we
gonna do it?

13:26.388 --> 13:28.057
{\an1}With the one thing
you guys do

13:28.140 --> 13:30.309
{\an1}better than anyone else
in the world.

13:30.392 --> 13:33.145
- Wash our feet
with tuna fish?

13:33.229 --> 13:34.605
- No.

13:34.688 --> 13:37.816
With the power of
a Hobo Pajama Dance Party!

13:37.900 --> 13:40.528
- But we don't know
how to dance.

13:40.611 --> 13:44.657
{\an1}- That's because you're
not wearing pajamas!

13:45.824 --> 13:47.076
<i>[bluegrass music]</i>

13:47.159 --> 13:48.160
- He's right!

13:48.244 --> 13:50.746
I'm a dancing machine!

13:50.829 --> 13:52.665
Bidi-bop-bop.

13:52.748 --> 13:54.166
- Who's with me?

13:54.250 --> 13:57.503
[all cheering]

13:57.586 --> 13:58.504
- Tickets!

13:58.587 --> 13:59.588
<i>[techno music]</i>

13:59.672 --> 14:02.591
What in the name
of techno ruckus is that?

14:02.675 --> 14:06.971
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:07.054 --> 14:11.600
How dare you celebrate noisily
in my train car.

14:11.684 --> 14:13.811
Let's get a whoopin'.

14:13.894 --> 14:15.187
- Not this time.

14:15.271 --> 14:18.274
Hobo Pajama Dance Party!

14:18.357 --> 14:20.317
Do the Crazy Bindle!

14:20.401 --> 14:24.446
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:24.530 --> 14:26.991
- Your 5:00 hobo shadows

14:27.074 --> 14:29.785
are like sandpaper!

14:29.868 --> 14:33.038
- Time for the
Hole in the Shoe Boogaloo!

14:33.122 --> 14:34.123
<i>[bluegrass music]</i>

14:34.206 --> 14:35.958
- Yeah!

14:36.041 --> 14:37.835
- [screams]

14:37.918 --> 14:39.545
[groaning]

14:39.628 --> 14:43.340
{\an1}- Now to top it off with
a Good Golly Miss Hog Molly!

14:43.424 --> 14:46.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:46.176 --> 14:47.303
Simple-de--

14:47.386 --> 14:49.179
- [grunts]
- [screams]

14:49.263 --> 14:51.140
- [growling]

14:51.223 --> 14:53.392
- I'm over here!

14:53.475 --> 14:54.977
- Here I am.

14:55.060 --> 14:56.353
Come and whoop me.

14:56.437 --> 14:58.355
My butt needs a whoopin'!

14:58.439 --> 14:59.940
- [growls]

15:00.024 --> 15:03.235
Oh, how dare you?

15:04.236 --> 15:06.989
[cheering]

15:07.072 --> 15:11.535
{\an1}- Banana, I hereby
declare you King of the Hobos.

15:11.619 --> 15:13.162
[cheering]

15:13.245 --> 15:15.706
- And King of TV!

15:15.789 --> 15:17.791
- Want wash your feet
in tuna fish?

15:17.875 --> 15:20.836
- I thought you'd never ask!

15:20.919 --> 15:22.546
[cheering]

15:23.672 --> 15:25.507
{\an1}- [laughs]

15:25.591 --> 15:26.467
Look at Banana.

15:26.550 --> 15:28.802
He thinks he's the King of TV.

15:28.886 --> 15:31.513
Well, he's about to be
overthrown.

15:31.597 --> 15:33.891
[chuckles]
Instead of busting my hump

15:33.974 --> 15:35.351
chasing the remote,

15:35.434 --> 15:39.396
I'll just build a program
to bring it to me.

15:39.480 --> 15:40.856
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:40.939 --> 15:43.776
[electricity buzzing]

15:43.859 --> 15:45.027
- On my state-of-the-art

15:45.110 --> 15:48.155
{\an1}Biomechanical Automated
Remote Finder.

15:48.238 --> 15:50.532
- Please, call me BARF.

15:50.616 --> 15:51.950
- Of course, BARF.

15:52.034 --> 15:53.202
Do your thing.

15:53.285 --> 15:54.411
{\an1}And hurry.
[laughs]

15:54.495 --> 15:56.538
{\an1}I really want to watch
The Goat Channel.

15:56.622 --> 15:58.957
- [beeping and grinding]

16:00.376 --> 16:02.211
[remote beeping]
- Hmm?

16:02.294 --> 16:03.629
[grunts]
Oh!

16:03.712 --> 16:05.506
- [beeping and buzzing]

16:05.589 --> 16:07.424
{\an1}- Oh, no,
what's wrong, BARF?

16:07.508 --> 16:10.135
{\an3}- I can't bring the remote
all the way here.

16:10.219 --> 16:13.430
I don't have enough power.

16:13.514 --> 16:14.431
- More power?

16:14.515 --> 16:15.057
What do you need?

16:15.140 --> 16:16.517
A radioactive battery?

16:16.600 --> 16:18.060
{\an1}A plutonium ion
processor?

16:18.143 --> 16:21.772
- Actually, I could really
go for a Cobb salad.

16:21.855 --> 16:23.941
- A Cobb salad?

16:24.024 --> 16:25.651
You mean chopped lettuce
with bacon bits

16:25.734 --> 16:26.944
in a light vinaigrette?

16:27.027 --> 16:28.362
{\an3}- Uh-huh.

16:28.445 --> 16:31.115
Why don't you take me
out for one, handsome?

16:31.198 --> 16:33.242
- Well, if that's
the only thing

16:33.325 --> 16:35.619
between me
and being King of TV,

16:35.703 --> 16:37.121
then let's Cobb it up!

16:37.204 --> 16:38.288
Hurry, come on!

16:38.372 --> 16:39.415
Get, get, get,
get, get, get, get!

16:39.498 --> 16:41.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:41.458 --> 16:43.585
Gobble that Cobble, BARF!

16:43.669 --> 16:46.797
{\an1}We need you juiced up
to get back that master remote.

16:46.880 --> 16:48.716
- You know, Cricket,

16:48.799 --> 16:50.759
you're quite
the dashing gentleman.

16:50.843 --> 16:54.054
[giggles]
And quite brilliant.

16:54.138 --> 16:56.265
- Wow, I am?

16:56.348 --> 16:59.601
Wow, BARF, I never realized
we have so much in common.

16:59.685 --> 17:03.605
We both like talking
about how smart I am!

17:03.689 --> 17:06.608
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

17:06.692 --> 17:09.278
- Whoops, look at that.

17:09.361 --> 17:10.695
{\an3}I dropped my
Cobb salad fork.

17:10.779 --> 17:12.948
- Here, let me help.

17:13.031 --> 17:15.451
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:15.534 --> 17:17.703
{\an1}- Hey Cricket,
who's your girlfriend?

17:17.786 --> 17:19.579
- Wha--wh--wh--what?

17:19.663 --> 17:21.915
- Ah!

17:21.999 --> 17:23.125
[spitting]

17:23.208 --> 17:24.334
- Sorry!
[chuckles]

17:24.417 --> 17:25.627
Girlfriend?

17:25.711 --> 17:28.464
You think this enormous
industrial supercomputer

17:28.547 --> 17:30.424
is my girlfriend?

17:30.507 --> 17:30.966
Oh, no.

17:31.049 --> 17:32.426
No, no, no, no.

17:32.509 --> 17:33.385
No, we're just friends.

17:33.469 --> 17:35.053
It's strictly professional.

17:35.137 --> 17:36.221
- What?

17:36.305 --> 17:39.183
{\an3}We are not strictly
professional.

17:39.266 --> 17:40.851
- [chuckling]
Oh, yeah.

17:40.934 --> 17:41.935
- That was weird.

17:42.019 --> 17:42.978
See you!

17:43.061 --> 17:46.148
- [chewing and crackling]

17:50.486 --> 17:52.196
- Whoa, hey, hmm.

17:52.279 --> 17:54.490
That's a lot
of Cobb salad.

17:54.573 --> 17:56.366
Is it cool if we
go halfsies on the bill?

17:56.450 --> 17:57.743
{\an3}- Halfsies?

17:57.826 --> 18:00.120
Now you're not even
paying for our date?

18:00.204 --> 18:01.663
[beeping and grinding]

18:01.747 --> 18:03.665
[cheering]

18:03.749 --> 18:05.250
- Hey!

18:05.334 --> 18:06.210
<i>My remote!</i>

18:06.293 --> 18:08.378
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:08.462 --> 18:09.379
- [screams]

18:09.463 --> 18:11.715
<i>♪</i> ♪

18:11.799 --> 18:13.175
[television beeping]

18:13.258 --> 18:14.176
- Huh?

18:14.259 --> 18:21.225
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:21.308 --> 18:22.184
- No, no!

18:22.267 --> 18:23.894
I just wanted the one remote,

18:23.977 --> 18:25.187
not all of them.

18:25.270 --> 18:26.396
BARF, what are you doing?

18:26.480 --> 18:28.857
You ate way too much
Cobb salad.

18:28.941 --> 18:32.236
<i>♪</i> ♪

18:32.319 --> 18:33.779
<i>Why are you doing this?</i>

18:33.862 --> 18:36.073
{\an3}Are you mad
or something, BARF?

18:36.156 --> 18:38.033
- You broke my heart, Cricket.

18:38.116 --> 18:40.077
I thought we had
something special.

18:40.160 --> 18:41.286
{\an3}- We do!

18:41.370 --> 18:42.788
{\an3}Oh, my gosh,
you know, I just--

18:42.871 --> 18:45.916
{\an3}I'm not ready for a
relationship right now.

18:45.999 --> 18:47.292
- Aw, Cricket.

18:47.376 --> 18:49.336
I didn't mean
to cause all this.

18:49.419 --> 18:51.046
{\an1}Why don't you
just deactivate me,

18:51.129 --> 18:51.839
then reactivate me
when you're ready

18:51.922 --> 18:54.550
to commit to our love.

18:54.633 --> 18:56.260
{\an3}- Well...
okay!

18:56.343 --> 18:58.303
{\an3}I mean,
if you insist.

18:58.387 --> 18:59.680
- Ah!

18:59.763 --> 19:02.391
{\an1}I can't believe you were
actually ready to unplug me.

19:02.474 --> 19:04.184
- But you told me to!

19:04.268 --> 19:05.644
- That was a test.

19:05.727 --> 19:08.522
{\an1}You're not putting any effort
into this relationship!

19:08.605 --> 19:11.441
- Why am I always
into the crazy ones?

19:11.525 --> 19:13.777
- I'll show you crazy!

19:13.861 --> 19:15.612
[beeping and grinding]

19:15.696 --> 19:17.739
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:17.823 --> 19:18.740
- Oh, no!

19:18.824 --> 19:20.033
{\an3}- Cricket!

19:20.117 --> 19:21.451
What's going on out--ow!

19:21.535 --> 19:23.203
There's hundreds
of remotes--ow!

19:23.287 --> 19:24.580
What is it, Pig?

19:24.663 --> 19:26.415
- Who's that mad lady?

19:26.498 --> 19:27.708
- [growling]

19:27.791 --> 19:28.750
{\an1}- Oh, that's Cricket's
new girlfriend.

19:28.834 --> 19:30.919
- [growling]

19:31.003 --> 19:31.920
[gasps]

19:32.004 --> 19:33.630
{\an1}- Oh, no,
we're just friends.

19:33.714 --> 19:34.631
{\an1}That's it.

19:34.715 --> 19:37.759
- Just friends?

19:37.843 --> 19:40.762
[growls]

19:40.846 --> 19:44.391
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:44.474 --> 19:45.392
- [sputters]

19:45.475 --> 19:50.272
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:50.355 --> 19:51.231
- Run!

19:51.315 --> 19:52.274
[all scream]

19:52.357 --> 19:56.612
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:56.695 --> 19:59.781
- I'll teach you
not to love me!

19:59.865 --> 20:01.909
{\an3}- It's controlling
the color saturation

20:01.992 --> 20:04.453
of the whole city!

20:04.536 --> 20:06.496
- I can defeat this monster...

20:06.580 --> 20:08.665
with the power of song.

20:08.749 --> 20:11.752
♪ Gumdrops, rainbows ♪

20:11.835 --> 20:14.379
♪ Fudge and remote control-- ♪

20:17.841 --> 20:19.468
- Wow, it muted her.

20:19.551 --> 20:21.094
Maybe BARF's
not so bad.

20:21.178 --> 20:24.348
- No one mutes my friend.

20:24.431 --> 20:28.143
{\an1}Prepare for trouble,
Pig style.

20:29.728 --> 20:32.773
{\an8}<i>Mi cabeza</i>
<i>es una pala gigante!</i>

20:32.856 --> 20:35.651
{\an3}- She just changed
Pig's channel!

20:35.734 --> 20:38.612
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:38.695 --> 20:40.155
[all murmuring]

20:40.238 --> 20:41.990
all: Huh?

20:42.074 --> 20:43.992
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:44.076 --> 20:45.410
- If I can't have Cricket,

20:45.494 --> 20:47.829
{\an1}then I'm turning
the world off forever!

20:47.913 --> 20:49.957
{\an1}- Well, this looks
like the end, fellas.

20:50.040 --> 20:52.709
Any second, she could
hit the On/Off button!

20:52.793 --> 20:54.127
{\an1}I'm sorry.

20:54.211 --> 20:55.963
{\an1}I never should've
made that master remote

20:56.046 --> 20:57.214
in the first place.

20:57.297 --> 20:59.341
{\an3}- We never should have
fought over it.

20:59.424 --> 21:03.178
{\an8}<i>- Yo era un cerdo,</i>
<i>pero ahora soy una pala.</i>

21:03.261 --> 21:05.263
{\an3}- If only we could
go back in time

21:05.347 --> 21:07.015
and make things right.

21:07.099 --> 21:08.016
- [gasps]

21:08.100 --> 21:09.351
Maybe we can,

21:09.434 --> 21:12.354
{\an3}with the help
of my trusty hobo skills.

21:12.437 --> 21:14.731
{\an3}Goat, give me
a good whoopin'!

21:14.815 --> 21:15.774
- Oh, yeah.

21:15.857 --> 21:17.234
I'm going to enjoy this.

21:17.317 --> 21:19.194
Wakataka whoop!

21:19.278 --> 21:20.696
- Hobo pole vault!

21:20.779 --> 21:23.907
<i>[bluegrass music]</i>

21:23.991 --> 21:25.158
- Trust me.

21:25.242 --> 21:28.203
{\an1}It never would have worked out
between you and Cricket.

21:28.286 --> 21:30.872
And now it's back
to the beginning.

21:30.956 --> 21:33.875
<i>[rock music]</i>

21:33.959 --> 21:39.214
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:39.298 --> 21:41.383
[all chewing and slurping]

21:41.466 --> 21:44.970
- Friends,
I have an announcement.

21:45.053 --> 21:49.307
Behold, the ultimate
master remote control.

21:51.309 --> 21:55.063
[all grunting and shouting]

21:55.147 --> 21:56.440
all: Pig Goat Banana Cricket,

21:56.523 --> 21:59.359
we smashed the remote
high five!

22:01.945 --> 22:04.948
{\an8}[gentle acoustic guitar music]

22:05.032 --> 22:13.040
{\an8}♪ ♪

22:25.218 --> 22:27.471
{\an8}[whoopee cushion whistles]
